1
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,966
[Episode 9: We're Just Colleagues]

2
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,891
I quit! I'm going home!

3
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:23,640
I'm done! I'm going home!

4
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:24,727
Isn't it?

5
00:01:24,727 --> 00:01:26,313
I...

6
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:32,509
I'm not going! I'm going home!

7
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:41,200
This...

8
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,920
is your home?

9
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,929
Of course not.

10
00:01:44,929 --> 00:01:47,240
After graduation,
I wanted to continue as a painter.

11
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,520
My dad insisted
that I take over his vinegar factory.

12
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,600
I refused.

13
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:52,240
So he cancelled my card.

14
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:54,768
I had to support myself.

15
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:59,175
I use the pink one.

16
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:02,920
Where were we?

17
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:03,960
Cancelled your card.

18
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:06,174
Yes. I had no money

19
00:02:06,174 --> 00:02:08,840
and didn't want to
live with my dad in the factory.

20
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:11,360
If I lived in the old house,
he could easily find me.

21
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:14,195
So I moved out and rented the house.

22
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:16,636
Thank you.

23
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:22,890
Are you selling the landlord's washing machine?

24
00:02:22,890 --> 00:02:26,247
It's mine from the old house.

25
00:02:26,247 --> 00:02:27,800
I don't like the old one.

26
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,480
I want to buy a new one.

27
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,270
You have a rich dad, don't you?

28
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:34,520
Why the secondhand?

29
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,520
Every penny saved counts.

30
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:39,300
Aren't you working in Florence?

31
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,879
I'm back for a break.

32
00:02:40,879 --> 00:02:42,360
A person working all day

33
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,400
is like a beast of burden.

34
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,018
That makes sense.

35
00:02:49,026 --> 00:02:50,680
What about you?

36
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:53,282
After graduation, I've been working here.

37
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:04,120
You asked me last time
about the relationship...

38
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,560
I have to go.

39
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,560
It's getting late.

40
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,596
I... take the washing machine.

41
00:03:12,024 --> 00:03:13,130
Thank you.

42
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:16,501
You made this pink too?

43
00:03:16,501 --> 00:03:18,815
Is it necessary?

44
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,960
<i>The rainy season is over.</i>

45
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:29,040
<i>It's summer in Nanwan.</i>

46
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:32,480
<i>It will be mostly sunny next week,</i>

47
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:35,252
<i>and the high will be around 30℃.</i>

48
00:03:35,252 --> 00:03:37,680
<i>Statistics show Nanwan received</i>

49
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,520
<i>18,000 visitors</i>

50
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,039
<i>in the two holidays this year.</i>

51
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:42,080
<i>And we're seeing</i>

52
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,218
<i>a soaring number of visitors...</i>

53
00:03:44,218 --> 00:03:48,560
[Nice to Meet You]

54
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,360
Nothing to do with me.

55
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:52,254
Something is wrong with this door.

56
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:02,276
Well, this old house

57
00:04:02,276 --> 00:04:06,120
has outdated facilities and renovations.

58
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,864
It needs renovation.

59
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:11,040
We don't have money for splurging, missy.

60
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,520
Not splurging!

61
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,400
It's investment!

62
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,916
You have money?

63
00:04:19,098 --> 00:04:21,209
Yes, I have money.

64
00:04:32,319 --> 00:04:36,040
I think we don't need many decorations here.

65
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,160
Just here.

66
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,279
Okay, okay.

67
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:39,920
And here.

68
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,520
Keep it concise. Keep it original.

69
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,814
- Here.
- Thank you.

70
00:04:42,814 --> 00:04:44,839
- Basically...
- You're a big help.

71
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:46,360
Otherwise we can't handle it.

72
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,920
And here...

73
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,960
Let's go.

74
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,720
Later, we can go for a walk.

75
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,710
- Other decorations...
- Okay.

76
00:04:52,710 --> 00:04:53,960
- Okay.
- Let's go.

77
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,060
Make changes here.

78
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:56,472
Okay. No problem.

79
00:04:56,472 --> 00:04:58,287
Mom, we're leaving.

80
00:04:58,287 --> 00:05:00,440
- Okay. Bye.
- Bye.

81
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,233
And the net, see?

82
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:06,908
So hot and annoying.

83
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,200
It'll be fine once the renovation is over.

84
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,600
No rush.

85
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,440
You guessed it?

86
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,785
I know it.

87
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,870
Like a cicada.

88
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,377
Who?

89
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,440
Me?

90
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,280
Us.

91
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:29,840
Cicadas spend 90% of their time

92
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,390
underground.

93
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:33,600
Seldom in trees.

94
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,072
Life is stagnant.

95
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,440
They live

96
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,164
for one moment.

97
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,932
And that moment...

98
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,416
What were you thinking just now?

99
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,545
Dry-fried cicadas.

100
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,385
What?

101
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,839
A specialty of Nanwan.

102
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:43,080
You can use it to attract customers.

103
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,581
Yeah.

104
00:06:44,581 --> 00:06:45,920
The locals aren't interested,

105
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,560
but tourists love it.

106
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,639
As a promotion,

107
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:50,400
free for each customer. What do you think?

108
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,140
It's summer, the peak tourist season.

109
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:57,551
How about... setting a time to discuss it?

110
00:07:04,472 --> 00:07:06,113
You're afraid of bugs?

111
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,880
I'm a bit busy lately.

112
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,860
For now, let's not make an appointment.

113
00:07:15,498 --> 00:07:17,119
Busy with what?

114
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,879
You just don't want to cook this.

115
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:23,155
Didn't you just submit your draft?

116
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:27,560
We're just colleagues.

117
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,397
I'm not obligated to report to you.

118
00:07:39,639 --> 00:07:42,759
Take it away! You know I'm afraid of bugs!

119
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:44,040
I'm desensitizing you.

120
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,685
Take it away!

121
00:07:47,563 --> 00:07:48,981
You're so afraid of bugs.

122
00:07:48,981 --> 00:07:50,120
Can you cook them?

123
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,544
Of course.

124
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,645
No.

125
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,051
You have to.

126
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:09,740
Clean the abdomen especially.

127
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,528
Mom!

128
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,796
Asleep so early.

129
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,323
Why does it taste a bit bitter?

130
00:08:39,323 --> 00:08:40,756
Bitter?

131
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,960
Heat oil to 150-180℃.

132
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,799
Fry over medium heat until set.

133
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:50,893
Then refry over high heat.

134
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,585
Fishy.

135
00:08:55,585 --> 00:08:57,098
Fishy?

136
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,965
Damn Xiang Nan Feng.

137
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,600
Chewy.

138
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:09,552
Chewy?

139
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,600
It stinks.

140
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,312
Tomorrow, tomorrow I'll make it better.

141
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:29,350
[Qiuping Diner]

142
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,510
Hey...

143
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:34,835
<i>Why is my dish different?</i>

144
00:10:40,101 --> 00:10:42,360
Me, Zhu Qiao Fei.

145
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,480
I'm back to run some errands

146
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,908
and drop by to see you.

147
00:10:45,549 --> 00:10:47,410
You have a nice place.

148
00:10:48,429 --> 00:10:49,578
Given by a brand.

149
00:10:49,578 --> 00:10:51,926
I can't finish it all. So I bring some to you.

150
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,790
I appreciate your kindness.

151
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:02,258
But I won't accept it.

152
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,705
Honey water.

153
00:11:07,705 --> 00:11:09,556
No sugar for me, sorry.

154
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,127
Then drink this water.

155
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,400
Mr. Xiang,

156
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,480
if you have a script,

157
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,270
would you consider me?

158
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,520
[Nanwan Liangpi]

159
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,840
<i>Damn Xiang Nan Feng.</i>

160
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,623
<i>You didn't reply to me.</i>

161
00:11:46,098 --> 00:11:48,911
Hello. How can I help you?

162
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,640
[Mancheng Co., LTD]
[General Manager: Zhong Yi]

163
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:05,428
<i>Zhong Yi?</i>

164
00:12:09,818 --> 00:12:13,213
Hey, have you heard that Zhong Yi returned too?

165
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:17,400
It's said to be team building with staff.

166
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,862
No big deal.

167
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:22,208
I... I just want to tell you...

168
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:24,200
Just chat.

169
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,734
Get to the point.

170
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:29,159
I want not a reserved role,

171
00:12:29,159 --> 00:12:31,200
but an audition chance,

172
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,559
for the fourth, fifth, or whichever male role.

173
00:12:33,559 --> 00:12:35,279
I act well, indeed.

174
00:12:35,279 --> 00:12:37,080
Talent will always find its way.

175
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,360
- Good luck.
- You doubt?

176
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,790
No.

177
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:42,072
As close classmates for three years,

178
00:12:42,072 --> 00:12:43,279
you know me well.

179
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:44,501
I value integrity.

180
00:12:44,501 --> 00:12:46,520
I tell the truth,

181
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:48,114
not lies.

182
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:52,440
Ren Xi Zhou definitely likes Zhong Yi.

183
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,254
Who is Zhong Yi?
